1 Introduction

The shot blocking data is obtained from the NHL stats site. We loop through all seasons from 2006-present and pull the regular season cumulative shot blocks for teams that played in the playoffs in each year.

2 Data pre-processing

2.1 Data normalizing

Well need to normalize this data so we can investigate across the different number of games in the regular season and the playoffs, and compare between the various teams that play a different number of games in the playoffs. To do this, well take the total of all the shot blocks in the regular season or playoffs and divide by the number of games in which those blocks were accumulated to get shot blocks per game.

df$blkPerGmRegular <- df$numBlocksRegular / df$numGamesRegular
df$blkPerGmPlayoff <- df$numBlocksPlayoffs / df$numGamesPlayoffs
df$blkDiff <- df$blkPerGmPlayoff - df$blkPerGmRegular

2.2 Plot the regular season and playoff data separately

par(mfrow=c(1,2))
hist(df$blkPerGmPlayoff, col = 'orange', main = 'Playoffs',
     xlab = 'Shot blocks per game',
     xlim = c(5, 25), ylim = c(0, 50))
hist(df$blkPerGmRegular, col = 'blue', main = 'Regular Season',
     xlab = 'Shot blocks per game',
     xlim = c(5, 25), ylim = c(0, 50))

2.3 Build combined data

dat <- data.frame(cond = c(rep('Regular Season', length(df$blkPerGmRegular)), 
                           rep('Playoffs', length(df$blkPerGmPlayoff))), 
                  PerGbm = c(df$blkPerGmRegular, df$blkPerGmPlayoff))

3 Histogram and density plots

3.1 Basic histogram from the vector PerGbm. Each bin is .5 wide.

ggplot(dat, aes(x=PerGbm)) + geom_histogram(binwidth=.5)

3.2 Draw with black outline, white fill

ggplot(dat, aes(x=PerGbm)) +
  geom_histogram(binwidth=.5, colour="black", fill="white")

3.3 Density curve

ggplot(dat, aes(x=PerGbm)) + geom_density()

3.4 Histogram overlaid with kernel density curve

ggplot(dat, aes(x=PerGbm)) + 
  geom_histogram(aes(y=..density..),
                 binwidth=.5,
                 colour="black", fill="white") +
  geom_density(alpha=.2, fill="#FF6666")

3.5 Add a line for the mean for histogram and density plots

ggplot(dat, aes(x=PerGbm)) +
  geom_histogram(binwidth=.5, colour="black", fill="white") +
  geom_vline(aes(xintercept=mean(PerGbm, na.rm=T)),   # Ignore NA values for mean
             color="red", linetype="dashed", size=1)

4 Histogram and density plots with multiple groups

4.1 Overlaid histograms

ggplot(dat, aes(x=PerGbm, fill=cond)) +
  geom_histogram(binwidth=.5, alpha=.5, position="identity") +
  ggtitle('2006-2015 NHL Shot Blocks Per Game For Playoff Teams') +
  labs(x = 'Shot Blocks per Game (Cumulative Shot Blocks / Games Played)', y = '%')

4.2 Interleaved histograms

ggplot(dat, aes(x=PerGbm, fill=cond)) +
  geom_histogram(binwidth=.5, position="dodge") +
  ggtitle('2006-2015 NHL Shot Blocks Per Game For Playoff Teams') +
  labs(x = 'Shot Blocks per Game (Cumulative Shot Blocks / Games Played)', y = '%')

4.3 Density plots

ggplot(dat, aes(x=PerGbm, colour=cond)) + geom_density() +
  ggtitle('2006-2015 NHL Shot Blocks Per Game For Playoff Teams') +
  labs(x = 'Shot Blocks per Game (Cumulative Shot Blocks / Games Played)', y = '%')

4.4 Density plots with semi-transparent fill

ggplot(dat, aes(x=PerGbm, fill=cond)) + geom_density(alpha=.3) +
  ggtitle('2006-2015 NHL Shot Blocks Per Game For Playoff Teams') +
  labs(x = 'Shot Blocks per Game (Cumulative Shot Blocks / Games Played)', y = '%')

4.5 Plot the Playoff - Regular Difference

ggplot(df, aes(x=blkDiff)) +
  geom_histogram(binwidth=.5, alpha=.2, col = 'blue', fill='green') +
  ggtitle('2006-2015 NHL Shot Blocks Per Game For Playoff Teams') +
  labs(x = 'Shot Blocks per Game (Cumulative Shot Blocks / Games Played)', y = '%')

5 Add lines for each mean requires first creating a separate data frame with the means.

5.1 Find the mean of each group

cdat <- ddply(dat, "cond", summarise, PerGbm.mean=mean(PerGbm))
cdat
##             cond PerGbm.mean
## 1       Playoffs    15.34194
## 2 Regular Season    13.51219

5.2 Overlaid histograms with means

ggplot(dat, aes(x=PerGbm, fill=cond)) +
  geom_histogram(binwidth=.5, alpha=.5, position="identity") +
  geom_vline(data=cdat, aes(xintercept=PerGbm.mean,  colour=cond),
             linetype="dashed", size=1)

5.3 Density plots with means

ggplot(dat, aes(x=PerGbm, colour=cond)) +
  geom_density() +
  geom_vline(data=cdat, aes(xintercept=PerGbm.mean,  colour=cond),
             linetype="dashed", size=1)

5.4 Using facets

ggplot(dat, aes(x=PerGbm)) + geom_histogram(binwidth=.5, colour="black", fill="white") + 
  facet_grid(cond ~ .)

5.5 With mean lines, using cdat from above

ggplot(dat, aes(x=PerGbm)) + geom_histogram(binwidth=.5, colour="black", fill="white") + 
  facet_grid(cond ~ .) +
  geom_vline(data=cdat, aes(xintercept=PerGbm.mean),
             linetype="dashed", size=1, colour="red")

6 Box plots

6.1 A basic box plot

ggplot(dat, aes(x=cond, y=PerGbm)) + geom_boxplot()

6.2 A basic box with the conditions colored

ggplot(dat, aes(x=cond, y=PerGbm, fill=cond)) + geom_boxplot()

6.3 The above adds a redundant legend. With the legend removed.

ggplot(dat, aes(x=cond, y=PerGbm, fill=cond)) + geom_boxplot() +
  guides(fill=FALSE)

6.4 With flipped axes

ggplot(dat, aes(x=cond, y=PerGbm, fill=cond)) + geom_boxplot() + 
  guides(fill=FALSE) + coord_flip()

6.5 Its also possible to add the mean by using stat_summary

Add a diamond at the mean, and make it larger

ggplot(dat, aes(x=cond, y=PerGbm)) + geom_boxplot() +
  stat_summary(fun.y=mean, geom="point", shape=5, size=4)

7 Does shot blocking look like it changes over the course of the last decade?

7.1 Build combined data

dat <- df %>%
  group_by(season) %>%
  arrange(season, blkPerGmRegular) %>%
  mutate(cond = as.character(season))

7.2 Box plots

ggplot(dat, aes(x=cond, y=blkPerGmRegular, fill=cond)) + 
  geom_boxplot() + guides(fill=FALSE)
